SIMPLE: merciless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Merciless
<hw>Mer"ci*less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Destitute of mercy; cruel;
unsparing; -- said of animate beings, and also, figuratively, of things;
<as>as, a <ex>merciless</ex> tyrant; <ex>merciless</ex>
waves.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The foe is <qex>merciless</qex>, and will not pity.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Cruel; unmerciful; remorseless; ruthless;
pitiless; barbarous; savage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mer"ci*less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mer"ci*less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercurammonium</ent>⟦br⟧
